.SH "NAME"
groblad \- record botanical observations
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.B groblad
.RB [ \-f
.IR template ]
.I file
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.B groblad
makes it convenient to record 
botanical observations into a text file
for future reference.
.P
Observations are grouped as a list of the species seen at a specific place and time.
The format and fields are based on
the paper field lists used during the census which ended up as
.IR "V\(:asterg\(:otlands Flora" ,
and on the
.I gavia
bird observation utilities (see
.BR gavia (1),
.BR gavia (5),
.BR gavia_stellata (1)).
.P
The basic idea is to fill in a template (using a text editor of your choice, which
.IR groblad
starts for you).
When you exit the editor, the observations are trimmed, syntax-checked,
and appended to
.IR file .
.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IP \-f\ \fItemplate
The template to start from.
If this option is not given, your personal template
.I ~/.flora
or the default template
.I lib/groblad/default
is used instead.
.
.SH "FILES"
.TP
.I ~/.flora
Personal excursion template file, on the format specified by
.BR groblad (5).
.TP
.I lib/groblad/default
Global excursion template file, used if the personal template isn't
available
and none has been given using the
.B \-f
flag.
.TP
.I INSTALLBASE/lib/groblad/species
The list of accepted species, subspecies, hybrids and forms.
This list is based on a subset of
Karlsson, T.
1997:
Svenska kärlväxter.
Svensk Bot. Tidskr. 91: 241\-560.
.RI ( http://www2.nrm.se/fbo/chk/ ).
.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.IP GAVIAEDITOR
Specifies the editor to use.
If not set,
.I VISUAL
or
.I EDITOR
is used instead.
If none of these are set, the default is
.BR emacs (1).
